	<div id="div-comment-4258">
	<span class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6ebed8c26658379ed2fe9989f8f634be?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48' height='48' width='48' />		<a href="#comment-4258" class="counter" title="Permanent Link to this Comment">6</a>
		<span class="commentauthor fn">A.J.</span>
	</span>
	<small class="comment-meta">
	<a href="#comment-4258" title="2 months, 3 weeks ago.">September 29, 2010 at 11:05 pm</a>	</small>

	<div class="comment-content">
		<p>Armindo, thanks for the pointer to disper &#8211; it works like a charm!  I wrote this little script that gets called on suspend/resume, and automatically fires up the external display if it&#8217;s connected:</p>
<p>#!/bin/sh<br />
ndisp=`/usr/bin/disper -l | grep display | wc -l`<br />
if [ $ndisp -ge 2 ]; then<br />
  /usr/bin/disper -e -t left<br />
else<br />
  /usr/bin/disper -s<br />
fi</p>
 
	</div>

	
